data.title: Better than usual Subway experience
data.text: Went there early Sunday around 10:30 AM the service was quick and friendly. I would definitely visit again.

data.title: It's Subway
data.text: The service was great, the workers were fast and friendly and the location is fantastic to run and and grab a quick bite

data.title: good food cheap but quality breads and veggies which are fresh
data.text:
a low cost sub style sandwich with many variations of meats and veggies can make a good quick meal at less than expected costs. The quality is very good for the money spent.
I like the meatball sandwich and my wife likes the turkey.The choice also included different styles of rolls all made in house and fresh. top it off with a cold drink and you are all set. eat in or take out,your choice.

data.title: Nice Food and service
data.text: The food and service just across the Kennedy Plaza is really good!  I loved their Chicken Cheese burger ....

data.title: typical chain sub shop
data.text: Other than their special of the week/month offerings, it is standard fare for a chain.  Counter order only. No seating.  All filling portions are pre measured.  A small sub will get you 3 slices of your meat choice, sometimes cheees is an additional charge.  Two slices of tomatoe, exactly 3 pickle slices, a pinch of shredded iceberg you get the picture.  The bread is fresh baked on site, sometimes under cooked and doughy.  The consistantency all depends on the manager and the counter staff.  Good idea for a beach pinic.  Other sub shops in my area offer larger portions to bread ratio.  Metza Metz

data.title: Quick dinner before concert
data.text: This Subway was right across the street from the hotel and when we couldn't get seated in the hotel restaurant (it was amazingly crowded and we couldn't wait for a table), this is where we went to get a bite before the concert. It was very sparingly furnished and slightly below street level. There was an almost constant noice coming from an undetermined source but the noise was pretty annoying. The food was standard Subway fare.

data.title: Good sandwiches. Good prices. Good nutritional choices.
data.text: Not exactly diet food, but a turkey sandwich on a whole wheat roll, loaded with veggies for 300 calories ain't half bad. Sandwiches made as you watch, how you instruct. Other, similar options. Good bonus point deals, too.
